more restrictive.\r\n\r\nIf the kerberos controller supports use non-conventional\r\nprincipal names *and the kerberos admin chooses to use them*\r\nthis can confuse some of the parsing.\r\n\r\nThe obvious solution is for the enterprise admins to \"not do that\"\r\nas a lot of things break, bits of hadoop included.\r\n\r\nHarden the hadoop code slightly so at least we fail more gracefully,\r\nso people can then get in touch with their sysadmin and tell them\r\nto stop it.", "tree": {"sha": "697d990fae954b3893cd70941afbaf6203163668", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/apache/hadoop/git/trees/697d990fae954b3893cd70941afbaf6203163668"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/apache/hadoop/git/commits/f7b1bb4dccc83eb26e661241ebf9f767f52b291b", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": true, "reason": "valid", "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsBcBAABCAAQBQJjmwgsCRBK7hj4Ov3rIwAAgCEIAAe/ZM5O0kWSD5uQh0+swDOt\nx+Uux8krpLAASOj7bb2M+lMfIow0WDjtfSGVYQSlBdIe/TDi+OUcosgJKvmlZn11\nzn1WHiD6AMU1GHfGnSYeB0SvPFO9wnOs+YQSX+89ogMxZx/GxttPKIt9weq68VNq\nrMxJ2nxWQ7cH9kJg9k6CpG0uCgw1YAVhbc6qXFObW/CvIiyW7R/lBQ4vQGYzmnsV\niRNMNWO3SMDsULTCL/RpFiW9R+Lnz90F7n37eKCv/1eVrDPVhHcyJ4gMgwvMB8/c\nVugH8OqUTuH94UPywRdO+9fuuAS6bXFvCB9MNKhBS298a8iNakELtadScHAKtmA=\n=01iv\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n", "payload": "tree 697d990fae954b3893cd70941afbaf6203163668\nparent 32414cfe46c6b691f6fa84896207941124dd1317\nauthor Steve Loughran <stevel@cloudera.com> 1671104556 +0000\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1671104556 +0000\n\nHADOOP-18573. Improve error reporting on non-standard kerberos names (#5221)\n\n\r\nThe kerberos RPC does not declare any restriction on\r\ncharacters used in kerberos names, though\r\nimplementations MAY be more restrictive.\r\n\r\nIf the kerberos controller supports use non-conventional\r\nprincipal names *and the kerberos admin chooses to use them*\r\nthis can confuse some of the parsing.\r\n\r\nThe obvious solution is for the enterprise admins to \"not do that\"\r\nas a lot of things break, bits of hadoop included.\r\n\r\nHarden the hadoop code slightly so at least we fail more gracefully,\r\nso people can then get in touch with their sysadmin and tell them\r\nto stop it.\r\n\r\n", "verified_at": "2024-11-06T18:14:48Z"}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/apache/hadoop/commits/f7b1bb4dccc83eb26e661241ebf9f767f52b291b", "html_url": "https://github.com/apache/hadoop/commit/f7b1bb4dccc83eb26e661241ebf9f767f52b291b", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/apache/hadoop/commits/f7b1bb4dccc83eb26e661241ebf9f767f52b291b/comments", "author": {"login": "steveloughran", "id": 162090, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2MjA5MA==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/162090?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveloughran", "html_url": "https://github.com/steveloughran", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveloughran/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveloughran/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveloughran/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveloughran/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveloughran/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveloughran/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveloughran/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveloughran/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveloughran/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "committer": {"login": "web-flow", "id": 19864447, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE5ODY0NDQ3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/19864447?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/web-flow", "html_url": "https://github.com/web-flow", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com